{"UserId":"43d98bd1-2838-409a-8f38-e7d49097353d","ChatId":"FC933163434F71536BBD04AEE4792119","Title":"","CreationTime":"2025-10-22T11:35:35.198Z","UpdateTime":"2025-10-22T11:46:50.885Z","ChatMode":{"chat_mode":"ludus_agent","display_text":"Ludus Agent","is_agent_mode":true},"Messages":[{"role":"user","message_blocks":[{"type":"text","content":"In Player_BP how do I get reference for cast to player_ABP"}]},{"role":"assistant","message_blocks":[{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b4-dde8-624e-bfff-e6e643e195fc"}},{"type":"text","content":"I'll help you get a reference to cast to Player_ABP from your Player_BP. Let me first examine your Player_BP to see its current structure."},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b4-de08-63aa-8000-944247a0d7c0"}},{"type":"tool_call","info":{"name":"read_blueprint","input":{"blueprint":"/Game/Blueprint/Player_BP.Player_BP","mode":"overview"},"reply_id":"tool_reply:read_blueprint:43d98bd1-2838-409a-8f38-e7d49097353d:FC933163434F71536BBD04AEE4792119:toolu_01PUBizxTHuX57SRteRHqzLx","metadata":null}},{"type":"tool_result","info":{"name":"read_blueprint"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-0f4b-6d93-8001-d021d176af40"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-2040-6c05-8002-875e6a8746c1"}},{"type":"tool_call","info":{"name":"read_blueprint","input":{"blueprint":"/Game/Blueprint/Player_BP.Player_BP","mode":"balanced"},"reply_id":"tool_reply:read_blueprint:43d98bd1-2838-409a-8f38-e7d49097353d:FC933163434F71536BBD04AEE4792119:toolu_01E1s7XYnthbiSam2xwqPHYd","metadata":null}},{"type":"tool_result","info":{"name":"read_blueprint"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-407f-6f38-8003-cc22e04533d6"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-505d-6587-8004-3f71235f5175"}},{"type":"text","content":"Looking at your Player_BP blueprint, I can see you have cast nodes for Player_ABP, but they're not connected to get the actual animation blueprint reference. Here's how to properly get a reference to cast to Player_ABP:\n\n## Steps to Get Animation Blueprint Reference:\n\n1. **Get Skeletal Mesh Component**: Since your Player_BP inherits from Character, you have a built-in Skeletal Mesh Component (usually called \"Mesh\").\n\n2. **Get Animation Instance**: From the Skeletal Mesh Component, get the Animation Instance.\n\n3. **Cast to Player_ABP**: Cast the Animation Instance to your Player_ABP class.\n\n## Blueprint Node Sequence:\n\n```\nSelf (Player_BP) \n→ Get Mesh (Skeletal Mesh Component)\n→ Get Anim Instance (Animation Instance)\n→ Cast to Player_ABP\n```\n\n## Specific Steps:\n\n1. Right-click in your blueprint and search for **\"Get Mesh\"** - this gets your character's skeletal mesh component\n2. Drag from the Mesh output and search for **\"Get Anim Instance\"** \n3. Drag from the Animation Instance output and search for **\"Cast to Player_ABP\"**\n4. Connect the execution pin to where you want to use this cast\n5. Use the \"As Player ABP\" output from the cast node to access your animation blueprint functions and variables\n\nThis will give you a proper reference to your Player_ABP animation blueprint that you can use to call functions, set variables, or access any custom functionality you've created in the animation blueprint.\n\nThe cast nodes you currently have (CastToPlayer_ABP_0 and CastToPlayer_ABP_1) need to have their Object input connected to the Animation Instance output from the Get Anim Instance node."},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-d459-67fc-8005-ea450db12fc0"}}]},{"role":"user","message_blocks":[{"type":"text","content":"Get anim instance does not exist so I tried creating animBPRef and assigning reference but for some reason it is saying that it will never work"}]},{"role":"assistant","message_blocks":[{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3b5-d459-67fc-8005-ea450db12fc0"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3cb-d1a4-6334-8007-2c647bb4414f"}},{"type":"text","content":"Let me help you get the animation instance reference properly. The function name might be slightly different than expected. Let me search for the correct way to get animation instances."},{"type":"tool_call","info":{"name":"knowledge_search","input":{"query":"get animation instance from skeletal mesh component blueprint character","mode":"default"},"reply_id":"tool_reply:knowledge_search:43d98bd1-2838-409a-8f38-e7d49097353d:FC933163434F71536BBD04AEE4792119:toolu_01JiDXPdBHGJy8qVn4bSn5Ag","metadata":null}},{"type":"tool_result","info":{"name":"knowledge_search"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3cc-2d40-6184-8008-f6530b3a0e4c"}},{"type":"text","content":"Perfect! I found the issue. The correct function is called **\"Get Anim Instance\"** from the Skeletal Mesh Component. Here's the exact sequence you need:\n\n## Correct Blueprint Node Sequence:\n\n1. **Get Mesh** (from your Character/Player_BP)\n   - This returns a SkeletalMeshComponent reference\n\n2. **Get Anim Instance** (from the SkeletalMeshComponent)\n   - Drag from the Mesh output and search for \"Get Anim Instance\"\n   - This returns a UAnimInstance reference\n\n3. **Cast to Player_ABP** (from the UAnimInstance)\n   - Drag from the Animation Instance output and search for \"Cast to Player_ABP\"\n\n## If you can't find \"Get Anim Instance\":\n\nTry searching for:\n- **\"GetAnimInstance\"** (one word)\n- **\"Animation Instance\"** \n- Look in the **Animation** category when right-clicking\n\n## Alternative Method - Using Variables:\n\nIf you're still having issues, try this approach:\n\n1. **Create a Variable**:\n   - In your Player_BP, create a new variable\n   - Set its type to **\"Player_ABP Object Reference\"**\n   - Name it something like \"AnimBPRef\" or \"PlayerAnimBP\"\n\n2. **Set the Variable in BeginPlay**:\n   ```\n   Event BeginPlay → Get Mesh → Get Anim Instance → Cast to Player_ABP → Set AnimBPRef\n   ```\n\n3. **Use the Variable**:\n   - Anywhere you need the Player_ABP reference, just use your \"AnimBPRef\" variable\n\n## Why it might say \"it will never work\":\n\nThis error usually occurs when:\n- The variable type doesn't match the cast output\n- The cast is failing (no valid animation blueprint assigned)\n- The skeletal mesh doesn't have an animation blueprint set\n\nMake sure your Player_BP's Mesh component has the Player_ABP assigned as its Animation Blueprint in the Details panel."},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3cc-324c-6db6-8009-92417174b58b"}},{"type":"checkpoint","info":{"id":"1f0af3cc-b22f-6fd9-800a-b520b58619b3"}}]}],"Mapping":{"node_agent_names":{"pairs":[{"first":"ADEFBBDA4B47762A07A05FBA01000DAB","second":"ConstructionScript_0"},{"first":"DE2F432B40720C3C2E667780E5C90E47","second":"CastToPlayerController_0"},{"first":"DEC63E6F4FA5D1C6D77CDAA69A3665B7","second":"EventBeginPlay_0"},{"first":"8660AE93468D1B3F20B2108487CA3DED","second":"IsValid_0"},{"first":"FBF899404F21A0667C42FCA5D8BF45B3","second":"GetController_0"},{"first":"8257F383485E00F09814F8937491D337","second":"GetEnhancedInputLocalPlayerSubsystem_0"},{"first":"087E7C7F4376411E23405C9894A062F4","second":"AddRerouteNode..._0"},{"first":"D00F24C04D6578B7A08E61A0DD8A08AE","second":"AddMappingContext_0"},{"first":"350400164DC7FDAB561AAB83387D9334","second":"AddControllerYawInput_0"},{"first":"937F6788444FB33B39C6F185182A3A83","second":"float*float_0"},{"first":"A16D28944928D07E71F5AFA0FF78FA74","second":"IA_Look_0"},{"first":"4E1B2A974ABE23DDC460CAAB0FA06136","second":"AddControllerPitchInput_0"},{"first":"1ECD54264029A3EB4897A9A22DBFF41C","second":"AddComment..._0"},{"first":"78BDDC734363B6813DCB21BBB26255A4","second":"DetectMovementKeys_0"},{"first":"DB6A58FA4243687BD5A780B90F680C4C","second":"AddRerouteNode..._1"},{"first":"E57749F14D22B9783FE9D48A8B02686D","second":"Set_0"},{"first":"3C4BDC7D4FD01B20D271A3AA6CC574BB","second":"AddRerouteNode..._2"},{"first":"11FC62734D52BD10F5F9E39E91E5D9DE","second":"IA_Move_0"},{"first":"9D66E01E4CCC35188EA69B94B79F81C0","second":"AddMovementInput_0"},{"first":"6B1402E54C319CF133DAD9B1F59FD2C6","secon